Package: odacore
Title: Pure-R Core Engine for Optimal Data Analysis (ODA / MultiODA)
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Nathaniel", "Rhodes", role = c("aut","cre"),
           email = "nrhode@midwestern.edu"),
    person("Paul", "Yarnold", role = c("ctb","cph"))
  )
Description: Provides a pure-R reimplementation of the MegaODA classification
    engine. Supports univariate binary-class ODA (UniODA) and univariate
    multiclass ODA (MultiODA) for ordered and categorical attributes, with
    priors-on inverse-frequency weighting, MAXSENS primary / SAMPLEREP
    secondary / first-identified tertiary tie-breaking, true leave-one-out
    (LOO) refit-per-fold cross-validation, Monte Carlo Fisher-randomization
    p-values with early stopping (STOP/STOPUP), and a full diagnostic harness
    for parity testing against MegaODA.exe golden outputs.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
Depends: R (>= 4.1.0)
Imports:
    stats,
    utils
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Config/testthat/edition: 3
RoxygenNote: 7.3.3
URL: https://github.com/njrhodes/ODA
BugReports: https://github.com/njrhodes/ODA/issues
